If you didn't know, back in 2020, I got on stage and competed in the Lee Haney Games.  For anyone who has prepared for competition, then you understand that it takes a different level of discipline and commitment to get up on that stage.  Although I haven't competed in a while, I still have a level of commitment and focus to maintaining a certain physique ALL YEAR ROUND! 
If I ever decide to grace that competition stage again, I'm never too far away from being stage ready. 💯
I don't allow myself to forget the fact that I wasn't supposed to be here.  I just Thank God that he has kept his hands on me. 🙏🏽

I don't deprive myself of everything that taste good.  Contrary to what you may think, I treat myself to a burger or something sweet every once in a while. The difference is I don't consume that stuff on a daily. The issue is people consume things that aren't good for their body daily. If you don't have discipline you cannot achieve success. Success requires discipline!
It doesn't matter who your favorite fitness person may be.  We all aim to achieve success and maintain our fitness one day at a time, one workout at a time.

Over the last 5 years I've had to be disciplined in ways that I didn't even know I was capable of.  God cleared the path for me and has removed obstacles out of my way because I stuck to his plan. Now I don't claim to be the most religious person in the world.  But I believe in God, I have experienced blessings beyond measure and I definitely have a testimony. 🙌
The definition of Consistency! 💯
